The sine function has values of 0 at integer multiples of pi, so the sum evaluates to:

\[ f(2) = \frac{4}{\pi} \left[ - \frac{\sin(\pi)}{1} + \frac{\sin(3\pi)}{3} - \frac{\sin(5\pi)}{5} + ... \right] = 0 \]

At t = 0, the top of the ladder is y(0) = 25 - 0 = 25 feet above the ground. When the top of the ladder is 7 feet below the top, the distance traveled by the top of the ladder will be 18 feet. Since y = 25 - x, dy/dx = -1. When t = 18 seconds, dy/dt = (-0.72 ft/s)/x = -0.72/(7/25) = -0.72 ft/s * (25/7 ft) = (180/7)*(-1/72) = (18/7) ft/s
